cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.DS 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.CV (Computer Vision) - The paper focuses on improving the quantization performance of deep neural networks for various vision tasks such as classification, detection, and segmentation. 
2. cs.LG (Machine Learning) - The proposed techniques involve reshaping the distribution of weights and activations, and splitting filters into groups to learn different quantization parameters, which are all related to machine learning. 
3. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) - The paper deals with improving the performance of low-bit quantization for deep neural networks, which is a key area of research in artificial intelligence. 
4. cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) - The proposed techniques involve modifying the weights and activations of neural networks, which is a key area of research in neural computing. 
5. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) - The proposed Group-based Quantization algorithm involves splitting filters into groups, which can be seen as a data structure.
